exitSurveyResponse.situations:
An common gripe about commenting code  is that it falls out of sync with the code. So if auto-summaries are VERY smart, then I'd use an auto-summary tool.

For example, if a summary tool CAN in fact summarize the method as /** Send a nuke to current location */ public void getAllResources() { icbm.setTarget(GPS.getCurrentLatLong()).launch(); }

Then by all means, auto-summarize for me!

generalThoughts:
When the arguments or the return value of the method is not obvious, or when they have special values. An example would be a method that returns a negative value as an error code or something like that (array.find() in javascript):  
<code>
// Return the index of the key, if found or -1 if not found
public int Array::indexOf( const char* key); 
</code>
Also when the method name is not self-explanatory or misleading, although i would avoid this situation in the first place if i could...

